tspan.tspan: Why Try BlueSky?
Join the Xodus at bsky.app
Like Old Twitter, BlueSky is an open
platform. There's an official app,
but there are others to pick from!
You pick your own Moderation
Service. BlueSky provides one, but if
you don't like it, you can just switch!
A billionaire could try to buy
BlueSky, but since it's open source,
anyone could spin up another copy.
You can own your own data by
setting up a Personal Data Server.
And your handle can be tied to your
domain name, so it can't be stolen.
BlueSky is supported by selling
advanced features, not your
attention and tracking.
There's no one "algorithm." You can
subscribe to Feeds which sort and
organize your content, or make one!
